## 7. Data Flow & Services

### API Client ([services/api.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/OneDrive/Desktop/Coding/Projects/Meili-AI/Meili-AI/frontend/services/api.ts))

The centralized API client handles all backend communication:
- **Auth**: `login()`, `signup()`, `logout()`, `refreshToken()`
- **Trips**: CRUD operations for trips/itineraries
- **Token management**: Auto-sets JWT on requests, auto-refresh every 25 minutes

### Data Sources (Current ‚Äî Mostly Mock)

Many pages currently load data from local JSON files:
- `lib/agent-dashboard/data/itinerary_data.json` ‚Äî itinerary data
- `lib/agent-dashboard/data/active_groups.json` ‚Äî active group trips
- `lib/agent-dashboard/data/upcoming_groups.json` ‚Äî upcoming group trips

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **For backend integration**: Replace these JSON imports with API calls through [services/api.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/OneDrive/Desktop/Coding/Projects/Meili-AI/Meili-AI/frontend/services/api.ts). The data structures in these JSON files define the expected shape of your API responses.

### Session Storage Keys

| Key | Set By | Used By |
|-----|--------|---------|
| `familyId` | Customer login | `customer-bookings`, `customer-itinerary` |
| `familyGroupMap` | Customer login | `customer-bookings`, `customer-itinerary` |
| `access_token` (localStorage) | [AuthContext](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/OneDrive/Desktop/Coding/Projects/Meili-AI/Meili-AI/frontend/contexts/AuthContext.tsx#15-24) | All authenticated requests |
| `agent_mock_trips` (localStorage) | New itinerary form | Agent dashboard |

